        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "Does this follow the Irving–Williams series? Yes—these data show the characteristic increase from Mn²⁺ → Cu²⁺ with a maximum at Cu²⁺, followed by a drop at Zn²⁺ (Irving–Williams: Mn < Fe < Co < Ni < Cu > Zn). Here Zn²⁺ lies between Co²⁺ and Ni²⁺, while Ni²⁺ and especially Cu²⁺ are stronger than the earlier metals, consistent with CFSE trends and the Jahn–Teller-stabilized Cu²⁺.",
